(c)
The torsion is zero.
</p></answer>

<solution><p>
(a), (b): <m>\hT</m> points in the direction of the curve; <m>\hN</m> is perpendicular to it, in the same plane, pointing towards the centre of curvature. Using the right-hand rule in the picture, we see <m>\hB</m> is pointing to the left.
</p>

<sidebyside width="46%">
